data.content:
Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne
The Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne is a legal document that determines the conditions for acquiring and losing Tunisian nationality.

Tunisian Nationality
Tunisian nationality is a legal status that can be acquired or lost after birth, according to the law and decisions made by the authorities.<SEP>Tunisian nationality refers to the legal status of being a citizen of Tunisia.

Article 1
Article 1 of the Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne defines individuals who have Tunisian nationality at birth as their nationality of origin.

Article 2
Article 2 of the Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne states that the conditions for acquiring and losing Tunisian nationality after birth are governed by the current law at the time of the relevant events and acts.

Article 3
Article 3 of the Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne states that new laws regarding the attribution of Tunisian nationality as nationality of origin apply to individuals born before the effective date of the laws, as long as they have not yet reached the age of majority.

Article 4
Article 4 of the Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne defines a person as an adult when they have reached the age of 18.

Article 5
Article 5 of the Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne defines the term 'in Tunisia' to include the entire Tunisian territory, territorial waters, and Tunisian boats, ships, and aircraft.

Article 6
Article 6 of the Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne, which has been replaced by the first article of the law n° 2010-55 of December 1, 2010, states that a child is Tunisian if their father or mother is Tunisian.

Article 7
Article 7 of the Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne states that a child born in Tunisia, whose father and grandfather were also born in Tunisia, is considered Tunisian.

Article 8
Article 8 of the Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne states that a child born in Tunisia to stateless parents who have resided in Tunisia for at least five years is considered Tunisian.

Article 9
Article 9 of the Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne states that a child born in Tunisia to unknown parents is considered Tunisian.

Article 10
Article 10 is a section of the document that pertains to the opposition process for violations of data protection norms in the registry.<SEP>Article 10 of the Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne states that a newborn child found in Tunisia is presumed to have been born in Tunisia until proven otherwise.

Article 11
Article 11 is a section of the document that outlines the specific data that is recorded and stored in the registry for each individual.<SEP>Article 11 of the Code de la Nationalite Tunisienne states that a child who is Tunisian under the provisions of this chapter is considered to have been Tunisian from birth, even if the conditions for Tunisian nationality are established after birth.

data.entity_name: Unité de gestion du Registre de l’identifiant unique citoyen
data.content:
Unité de gestion du Registre de l’identifiant unique citoyen
L'Unité de gestion du Registre de l’identifiant unique citoyen est une unité créée au sein du ministère chargé des affaires locales, chargée de gérer le Registre et la base de données de l'état civil, mettre en place des mécanismes d’attribution de l'identifiant, assurer la qualité, la sécurité et la mise à jour des données du Registre, assurer le bon fonctionnement du système d'information de l’identifiant unique citoyen, mettre en place des mécanismes d'accès aux données du Registre conformément à la législation et réglementation en vigueur, mettre en place les mécanismes nécessaires permettant aux personnes de consulter les opérations relatives à leurs données personnelles, leur historique et l’identité de l’organisme ayant procédé à l’accès, encourager l'utilisation des services liés à l’identifiant, et présenter des propositions dans le cadre de la stratégie d'utilisation de l'identifiant.<SEP>The Unité de gestion du Registre de l’identifiant unique citoyen is a unit created within the ministère chargé des affaires locales, responsible for managing the Registre and the civil status database, implementing mechanisms for assigning the identifier, ensuring the quality, security, and updating of the Registre data, ensuring the proper functioning of the unique citizen identifier information system, implementing mechanisms for accessing the Registre data in accordance with applicable legislation and regulations, establishing the necessary mechanisms for individuals to consult the operations related to their personal data, history, and the identity of the organization that accessed it, promoting the use of services related to the identifier, and making proposals within the framework of the identifier's use strategy.<SEP>The Unité de gestion du Registre de l’identifiant unique citoyen is a unit within the ministry responsible for managing the Registre de l’identifiant unique citoyen and ensuring compliance with data protection regulations.

Article 12
Article 12 is a section of the document that specifies the duration for which the data is retained in the registry.

Article 13
Article 13 is a section of the document that assigns the responsibility of managing the registry to the minister in charge of local affairs and outlines the use of a digital platform for its management.

Article 14
Article 14 is a section of the document that establishes the probative value of the data recorded in the registry and its potential use as an alternative to paper records.

Article 15
Article 15 is a section of the document that addresses the process for reporting any discrepancies between the data in the registry and paper records.

Article 16
Article 16 is a section of the document that outlines the timeline for updating the data in the registry by the civil registration officers.

Article 17
Article 17 is a section of the document that specifies the authorized entities that can access the data in the registry for the purpose of carrying out their duties.

Article 18
Article 18 is a section of the document that defines the conditions and procedures for accessing the data in the registry in accordance with data protection legislation.

Article 19
Article 19 is a section of the document that prohibits organizations from demanding citizens to provide data that is already recorded in the registry.

Article 20
Article 20 is a section of the document that requires the recording of all operations related to the consultation, update, modification, or transmission of personal data in the registry.

Article 21
Article 21 is a section of the document that outlines the obligations of the authorized entities to facilitate the control missions of the Instance nationale de protection des données à caractère personnel.

Article 22
Article 22 is a section of the document that requires the authorized entities to conduct periodic security audits of their information systems and networks in accordance with relevant cybersecurity legislation.

Centre national de l’informatique
Le Centre national de l’informatique est chargé des missions techniques et opérationnelles liées à la gestion du registre, sous la supervision de l’Unité de gestion du Registre de l’identifiant unique citoyen.<SEP>The Centre national de l’informatique is responsible for the technical and operational missions related to the management of the Registre, under the supervision of the Unité de gestion du Registre de l’identifiant unique citoyen.
